  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multisectoral lifesaving assistance in response to emergency influx of Burundi refugees in Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CERF funds will support UNHCR&apos;s multi-sector assistance to 30,000 newly arrived Burundian refugees in Rwanda.  Activities will be carried out at the Bugesera and Nyanza reception centres and the new Mahama refugee camp.  In particular, UNHCR and partners will register refugess and transport them to the centres or camp, provide safe water and sanitation facilities, carry out emergency nutrition and health screenings, prepare land for the camp, and distribute shelter materials, relief items and firewood.  UNHCR is the primary lead in providing assistance in this refugee operation while other UN agencies are providing specialized support in their areas of technical expertise.</narrative>
  </description>
